Posted: August 23, 2021
Worms: Ultimate Mayhem is a masterpiece game of my childhood. I still played this game when I was 9 years old (somewhere in 2014-2015). I remember when my parents bought me a disk with all the parts of Worms. The most favorite for me were Worms 2 and this masterpiece. But let's get to the point.

This game is the best 3D game in this series of games. A fun turn-based strategy game that will not let you get bored in the company of friends. But if you don't have any friends, then you can play a good campaign with a good plot. There is also a plot from Worms 3D, but this is for an amateur, I personally liked it. Next, I would like to talk about the pluses and minuses of this game.

Pluses:
1. Minimum system requirements (which is logical, because the game is 2011 and will be able to run on your Pentium);
2. Fun. In this game there are several ways to make fun or kill your opponent, which gives quite a few fun strategies;
3. Random map generator. Of course, there are enough maps in this game, but the feature of this game is a map generator that places objects in a random place. This makes the game much more diverse;
4. The ability to create your own team and weapons. Of course, it's obvious with the team here, you create your own worms, give them names, a voice, hang caps on them (which you can buy in the store for coins earned in story missions), etc.. But with weapons it's more interesting: you can give them recoil, damage, explosion force and many other functions. Of course, many people will say that it is possible to make an unbalanced gun, but this is not so. There is a meter that is responsible for the" killing power " of the gun. If you make a gun to powerful, the meter will wedge and will not give you opportunities to create your own weapons, so adjust wisely :);
5. Since this is a turn-based strategy, in addition to boundless fun, you also need to think in some situations how to make a move and what is better to use, so you can strain your brains a little

Minuses:
1. The number of players online is low, but this can not be considered a minus if you play with friends, but still if you want to play with random, then you will have to look for a long time;
2. There are few game modes in the game, somewhere 5-6, but they usually play only in deathmatch. This, of course, is upsetting;
3. There are bugs here too. My friend, for example, if he wanted to take a screenshot in full-screen mode and send it to me in discord, then he had a black screen instead of a screenshot and when he returned to the game, he had no sound. Of course, we fixed this by switching to windowed mode (there also seems to be no resolution of 1920x1080, but for me personally this is not a problem, maybe I'm wrong);
4. You can't adjust the sensitivity of the mouse here, but there is no big difference for me, because I can adjust the DPI on the mouse, but before I was comfortable without it.

What can I say? Personally, I have always liked this series of games and all the games before Revolution cause me nostalgia. The game can still raise a smile on your face. It is as interesting as it has been since the last time I played it. I recommend this project to purchase, as well as to your friends, so that you can get together and have fun together.

9 holy grenades out of 10
